ce wird anhand von Eustathios, Ermolao Barbaro, Erasmus und weiteren belesenen Autoren nachgezeichnet.  aThe Ethnica by Stephanus of Byzantium constitute a dictionary of geography and cultural history from the Justinian period that has been transmitted to us in abridged form. They record place names and terms of belonging (ethnica), generally using "es from source authors. Alongside their value as a source of lexicographical information, where authors' works have been lost, the Ethnica are hugely significant as a source of fragments.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 4aGriechische Grammatik. 4aLexikographie. 4aStephanus Byzantinus. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aGreek grammar.  aStephanus of Byzantium.  alexicography.1 aNeumann-Hartmann, Arlette, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2021z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021z97831107538130 cEPUBz97831107277390 cprintz978311072685540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311072767840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110727678423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110727678.jpg  a978-3-11-075070-6  DG Ebook Package 2021b2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  a978-3-11-075381-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK